Install pigpio: (from official page: "initial part of the make takes 100
seconds on early model Pis. Be patient. The overall install takes just over
3 minutes")

wget abyz.co.uk/rpi/pigpio/pigpio.zip
unzip pigpio.zip
cd PIGPIO
make -j4
sudo make install

ir_sender based off
https://blog.bschwind.com/2016/05/29/sending-infrared-commands-from-a-raspberry-pi-without-lirc/
https://github.com/bschwind/ir-slinger

ir_reader also from ^, format modified for analysis purposes

ir_sender library implements:
 NEC Protocol, RC5 Protocol

samples made for NEC protocol and a cheap light device:

BINZET 5M 50 LEDs 3AA Battery Operated Copper Wire String Light LED (...)
with Remote Control.
Pros: Cheap, remote control is 3.3v (same as rpi gpio)

range roughly 4m
